## Code Style Rules
- Always use functional components with arrow functions
- Use TypeScript interfaces for all props -- never use `any`
- Use `const` by default, `let` only when reassignment is needed
- Never use `var`
- Always add clear comments explaining what each section does
- Keep components small and single-purpose

## Next.js Rules
- App Router always -- never use Pages Router patterns
- Use next/image for every image -- never use plain <img> tags
- Use next/link for all internal links -- never use plain <a> tags
- Server components are the default
- Only add "use client" when necessary (animations, useState, useEffect)
- Use Next.js Metadata API for SEO -- never manually write <head> tags
- Never use getServerSideProps or getStaticProps (deprecated)

## Styling Rules
- Mobile-first always -- base styles for mobile, md: and lg: for larger screens
- Use Tailwind spacing scale -- avoid arbitrary values like w-[347px] unless truly necessary
- Never use inline styles
- RTL-ready: use logical CSS properties (padding-inline-start not padding-left)

## Animation Rules
- GSAP + ScrollTrigger for all scroll-driven animations
- Framer Motion for component transitions, nav animations, hover states
- Always respect prefers-reduced-motion -- disable all animations when set
- Wave parallax scroll speed factors: wave-100: 0.2, wave-200: 0.35, wave-300: 0.5, wave-400: 0.65, wave-500: 0.8, wave-600: 1.0

## What To Avoid
- Never install packages without asking first
- Never use TypeScript `any` type
- Never use deprecated Next.js patterns
- Never use plain CSS when Tailwind can do the job
- Never use <img> or <a> tags for internal content